article.headline: Texas builds 27-point halftime lead
article.linkText: Six reach double figures as Longhorns roll
article.story:
AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- Kala Bowers scored 24 points and was one of
six Longhorns in double figures Sunday as Texas (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) trounced Southeastern Louisiana on 106-42.

	   Heather Schreiber had 16 points for Texas (4-2), while Mercedes
Williams had 14, Coco Reed 13, Stacy Stephens 12 and Tamra Cobbins
10.

	   Pam Mathews had 15 points for Southeastern Louisiana (1-5),
while Velicity Burkhalter added 11.

	   Texas led 49-22 at halftime.

	   The Longhorns had 42 points turnovers while Southeastern
Louisiana managed just 3. Texas also finished with a 30-2 advantage
in fast break points.
